<html><body><h2>persist7.jsp receives only an InfoBean object in its session.<br />The last page showed how we build a bean property by property.<br />This page will delete the old bean and submit all its properties to persist8.jsp as form fields.<br />Then we'll see how easy it is to create a bean in one step when all its properties are in the request!</h2><jsp:useBean id="infobean" class="edu.acc.j2ee.persist.InfoBean" scope="session"/><form action="persist8.jsp" method="POST"><input type="hidden" name="firstName" value="<jsp:getProperty name="infobean" property="firstName"/>"/><input type="hidden" name="lastName" value="<jsp:getProperty name="infobean" property="lastName"/>"/><input type="hidden" name="age" value="<jsp:getProperty name="infobean" property="age"/>"/><input type="hidden" name="city" value="<jsp:getProperty name="infobean" property="city"/>"/><% session.removeAttribute("infobean"); %><input type="submit" value="Submit bean properties as form fields"/></form></body></html>